                                                                <comments>
                            <comment id="13446061" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 16:42:57 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Patch introduces concept of closed and unclosed LedgerFragment. An unclosed LedgerFragment cannot be rereplicated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446062" author="umamaheswararao" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 16:43:39 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;@Ivan, We will not replicate the fragment which is open and last fragment is in under replication. I am handling this in &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-325&quot; title=&quot;Delay the replication of a ledger if RW found that its last fragment is in underReplication.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-325&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-325&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446072" author="ikelly" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 16:55:40 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;I saw, but I decided it needed to be enforced at a lower level also. I&apos;ve left a comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-325&quot; title=&quot;Delay the replication of a ledger if RW found that its last fragment is in underReplication.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-325&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-325&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13446098" author="umamaheswararao" created="Fri, 31 Aug 2012 17:26:11 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Ok, thanks a lot Ivan. I will take a look at this patch. I actually expected this ledger open detection from LedgerChecker, when we were implementing that. I think that time we were in diff &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-247?focusedCommentId=13405001&amp;amp;page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel#comment-13405001&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;thought&lt;/a&gt;. I am fine with this approach too. I will review it tomorrow.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13447275" author="umamaheswararao" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 14:41:48 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Hi Ivan,&lt;br/&gt;
I looked at the patch. It looks good to me.&lt;br/&gt;
I have 2 small modifications in the patch&lt;br/&gt;
 1) I feel, we need not really expose 2 more static APIs for separating closed/unclosed fragment creations. Anyway we are passing the ledgerHandle to LedgerFragment, so we can make the decision from LedgerFragment itself and callers need not really worry about it, what kind of fragments they are. I think it is bit cleaner for me.&lt;br/&gt;
 2) modified the test to have more fragments instead of single one, so, that we can ensure last only one last unclosed fragment failed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt; 3) BTW cleaned some unused imports.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Attached a patch by modifying it. Check if you like that changes.&lt;br/&gt;
Other than that, previous Patch looks great to me. &lt;/p&gt;


&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot,&lt;br/&gt;
Uma&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13447345" author="ikelly" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 17:33:11 +0100"  >&lt;blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;1) I feel, we need not really expose 2 more static APIs for separating closed/unclosed fragment creations. Anyway we are passing the ledgerHandle to LedgerFragment, so we can make the decision from LedgerFragment itself and callers need not really worry about it, what kind of fragments they are. I think it is bit cleaner for me.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/blockquote&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Makes sense. However, in the implementation, you have two boolean fields where only one is needed, as #isClosed() is doing the same boolean logic every time. How about just having a single boolean isClosed field, and calculating it in the constructor?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;
SortedMap&amp;lt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Long&lt;/span&gt;, ArrayList&amp;lt;InetSocketAddress&amp;gt;&amp;gt; ensembles = lh.getLedgerMetadata().getEnsembles();
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.isClosed = lh.getLedgerMetadata().isClosed() || !ensemble.equals(ensembles.get(ensembles.lastKey()));
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13447355" author="umamaheswararao" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 18:11:26 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, sounds good to me. As I already have the same code applied in my eclipse, I just generated again the patch with addressing the above comment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks a lot,&lt;br/&gt;
Uma&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13447376" author="ikelly" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 19:12:02 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/secure/ViewProfile.jspa?name=umamaheswararao&quot; class=&quot;user-hover&quot; rel=&quot;umamaheswararao&quot;&gt;Uma Maheswara Rao G&lt;/a&gt; Previous patch is incompatible with &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-385&quot; title=&quot;replicateLedgerFragment should throw Exceptions in error conditions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-385&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-385&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. New patch fixes the compile issues. Will commit once you +1.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13447378" author="umamaheswararao" created="Mon, 3 Sep 2012 19:26:16 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Yeah, It look like I just generated it before the commit of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/BOOKKEEPER-385&quot; title=&quot;replicateLedgerFragment should throw Exceptions in error conditions&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;BOOKKEEPER-385&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;BOOKKEEPER-385&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;img class=&quot;emoticon&quot; src=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/images/icons/emoticons/smile.gif&quot; height=&quot;16&quot; width=&quot;16&quot; align=&quot;absmiddle&quot; alt=&quot;&quot; border=&quot;0&quot;/&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 for the patch.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13447562" author="ikelly" created="Tue, 4 Sep 2012 09:39:59 +0100"  >&lt;p&gt;Committed as r1380488. Thanks for your input on this Uma.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
